rom-baby-to-dog-miracle-rescues-giving-venezuela-hope-after-deadly-earthquakes-watch/articleshow/132006633.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-26T09:45:33+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132007005,imgsize-3599843.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[End of an era: King Charles breaks 180-year tradition, will not live in Buckingham Palace]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132006518.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/end-of-an-era-king-charles-breaks-180-year-tradition-will-not-live-in-buckingham-palace/articleshow/132006518.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/end-of-an-era-king-charles-breaks-180-year-tradition-will-not-live-in-buckingham-palace/articleshow/132006518.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-26T09:24:15+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132006536,imgsize-109076.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Venezuela quake leaves 235 dead: Thousands feared trapped as rescue efforts intensify]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132005572.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Northern Venezuela grapples with devastation after twin earthquakes, with the death toll climbing past 235 and thousands feared affected. Rescue efforts are underway, though residents report slow official responses. International aid is pouring in, with the US authorizing significant assistance and numerous countries dispatching rescue teams. Despite widespread destruction, the nation's vital oil infrastructure remains largely intact.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/venezuela-quake-leaves-235-dead-thousands-feared-trapped-under-rubble-as-rescue-efforts-intensify/articleshow/132005572.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/venezuela-quake-leaves-235-dead-thousands-feared-trapped-under-rubble-as-rescue-efforts-intensify/articleshow/132005572.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-26T07:22:39+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132005627,imgsize-1811940.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA["The final year of Charlie’s life....": Candace Owens raises doubts over TPUSA staffer's story of Charlie Kirk's final hours]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132005201.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Candace Owens has questioned Turning Point USA spokesperson Andrew Kolvet's account of Charlie Kirk's alleged final text message, claiming his public statements differ from what he privately told her after Kirk's death. Owens said Kolvet initially admitted he was unsure who Kirk was referring to, but later claimed the message referenced leftists. Kolvet has defended his position publicly, while the exchange has reignited debate over the circumstances surrounding Kirk's final hours.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/the-final-year-of-charlies-life-candace-owens-raises-doubts-over-tpusa-staffers-story-of-charlie-kirks-final-hours/articleshow/132005201.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/the-final-year-of-charlies-life-candace-owens-raises-doubts-over-tpusa-staffers-story-of-charlie-kirks-final-hours/articleshow/132005201.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-26T05:31:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Barsha Dutta</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132005201,imgsize-97869.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA["Serve me some dog sh*t": Kick streamer Clavicular goes viral for brutal review of French restaurant's organic burger]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132005209.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Kick streamer Clavicular went viral after criticizing an organic burger served at a high-end French restaurant, calling it "barely edible" and saying McDonald's tasted much better. During his livestream, he complained about the burger falling apart and questioned the restaurant's upscale service despite his poor dining experience. The clip quickly spread across social media, sparking debate over whether expensive restaurants always offer better food than fast-food chains.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/serve-me-some-dog-sht-kick-streamer-clavicular-goes-viral-for-brutal-review-of-french-restaurants-organic-burger/articleshow/132005209.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/serve-me-some-dog-sht-kick-streamer-clavicular-goes-viral-for-brutal-review-of-french-restaurants-organic-burger/articleshow/132005209.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-06-26T05:52:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Barsha Dutta</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132005209,imgsize-70616.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA['Took Rs 1.24 cr education loan': F-1 visa denied after Indian student reveals family income to visa officer]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132003035.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CD